box iron
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: As I remember them, not always as OED2 `with cavity for hot coals in them', but mainly squat shape with sides taller (or the iron deeper) than the ordinary flat-iron, and often `double ended' rather than triangular, and differing from a flat-iron in having detachable handles. (HWO)
