Quote:   The first ironing that I remember was done with what we called a `box iron' - steel frame much like the shape of the present-day iron, although rather shorter and deeper.
Notes:  1940 McBride in Tales of Pioneer Women in 1974 Heinz Bright Fine Gold 17
